		{
			dependencies: ["0A47F74F64457575"]
			description: [
				"To build a Smeltery you need to create a closed enclosure with floor and wals from seared blocks with controller, fuel tank, chutes and drains. The quest requires you to craft minimal amount, but you can always expand the smeltery in all directions which give it more storage and slots for simultaneous smelting."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"Smeltery use lava as fuel to melt any resources down. Put it in &oFuel Tank&r."
				""
				"Clicking the Controller will open its UI, where you can put meltable things manually or provide items throught &oChute&r with various means like hoppers. &l!!!BE CAREFUl!!!&r Metals will become alloys automatically after smelting, so look what you put there."
				""
				"After they become liquids you can click on them in the UI to change their order. Those at the very bottom will get poured out of the &oDrain&r, but only if there Faucet on them and Casting Table or Basin to pour."
				""
				"You can give Faucet a redstone signal (like putting lever near) to automatically pour out of Smeltery. "
			]
			icon: "tconstruct:smeltery_controller"
			id: "25B2030958956699"
